The Raspberry Pi is a single board credit card sized microcomputer developed in UK by Raspberry Pi Foundation in 2012. Raspberry Pi is an ARM Architecture Processor based board, a cpu of 1.2 giga hertz, 1 GB RAM and supports SD cards as external hard drive.
